      "id": "d9fb5fc883766fff522bbd65a8d606970a11bdde",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 109,
        "name": "Christopher J. Morrone",
        "email": "morrone2@llnl.gov",
        "username": "morrone"
      },
      "date": "2016-01-28 19:32:47.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\nAny change in this area needs to be compatible with LU-5614, and this one is not.\n\nAlso, I am really reluctant to approve allow a commit that adds configure options that have no impact on Lustre's configuration.  This option only exists to be passed along to the packaging system, and I think that is really moving things in the wrong direction.\n\nI think it would be better to move towards having multiple, simpler rpm files.  One rpm file might avoid weak-module packaging altogether, and be more friendly to the day-to-day needs of the developers.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
